Programming Language: Python

How to execute our program:

	python cipher.py <CIPHER NAME> <KEY> <ENC/DEC> <INPUT FILE> <OUTPUT FILE>

	  where:
		<CIPHER NAME> = {DES,AES} # the name of the cipher
		<KEY> = {
			DES: 16 characters representing a 64-bit hexadecimal number
      AES: 32 characters representing a 128-bit hexadecimal number
			No Quotes around kNo 
		} # the encryption key to use
		<ENC/DEC> = {ENC, DEC} # whether to encrypt or decrypt, respectively
		<INPUT FILE> = the file from which to read the input
		<OUTPUT FILE> = the file to which the output shall be written

	  examples:

		DES
		python cipher.py DES 0123456789abcdef ENC input.txt output.txt

		AES
		python cipher.py AES 0123456789abcdef0123456789abcdef DEC input.txt output.txt

